description: With power applied and the switch closed, use a voltmeter to identify which of the two cables coming out of the power supply module is at +12 V relative to the other, then trace that same conductor through the control module to the load module to determine whether the load’s series diode is correctly oriented with respect to the actual +12 V line or if the polarity between modules is swapped., outcome='The PSU Output Cable (+) is at +11.99 V relative to the PSU Output Cable (−), and this same polarity is preserved through the Control Input Cables to the load, with no POLARITY INVERSION DETECTED between modules. At the load, the positive line is present on Load Input Cable (+) (~0.36 V relative to Load Input Cable (−)), indicating the load’s series protection diode is oriented with its anode toward the control output and its cathode toward the load as expected. The load protection diode itself tests nominal with a forward voltage of 0.7 V.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=200.0, cost_breakdown=[('close_switch', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_diode', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
